%N A396157 Triangle; T(n,m) is the number of possible outcomes having a run of m or more heads when a coin is tossed n times.
%C A396157 See also A396158: number of possible outcomes having a run of m or more sixes when a die is rolled n times.
%H A396157 Félix Balado and Guénolé C. M. Silvestre, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.10005">Systematic Enumeration of Fundamental Quantities Involving Runs in Binary Strings</a>, arXiv:2602.10005 [math.CO], 2026.
%F A396157 T(n,m) = A001792(n-m) for ceiling(n/2) <= m <= n.
%F A396157 T(2*n+1,n) = A001792(n+1) - 1.
%F A396157 T(n,0) = A000072(n).
%F A396157 T(n,1) = A000225(n) = 2^n - A000012(n).
%F A396157 T(n,2) = A008466(n) = 2^n - A000045(n+2).
